As women's history month comes to a close, I'm reminded of the strength and resilience of women, in particular Black women who push beyond the walls and barriers that life sometimes throws at them- for a cause bigger than themselves. Earlier this week I caught up with the writer/director @avrockwell and star @teyanataylor of the upcoming coming-of-age story @athousandandonefilm to discuss why it was important to tell this story and the journey and challenge of taking on the role of “Inez”. These women pushed through barriers to deliver a story of self-discovery, love, pain, and joy. I wish I had more time because I definitely had more questions to ask. You will see yourself or someone you know in these characters! “A Thousand And One” lands in theaters tomorrow 3.31.23. 
🎥 @whereisthebuzztv 
XoAD💋
.
.
.
.
.

October is Breast Cancer Awareness Month, and tomorrow’s special episode of @undunnwithashleydunn is dedicated to raising awareness about breast cancer. 

Join me and special guest, 13 year stage 4 breast cancer survivor and 25 year US Air Force Veteran @sheila_marie_johnson as we delve into this important topic and shed light on the latest advancements in treatment, prevention, and support. 

Sheila, brings a wealth of knowledge and expertise, sharing valuable insights on early detection, screening techniques, treatment options, and survivorship. Sheila’s story is so inspiring, so much so that it’s been adapted into a movie. "God's Grace: The Sheila Johnson Story," is set to premiere tomorrow on October 19th on @betplus @bet.

Breast cancer affects millions of people and their families worldwide. By listening to this episode, you'll gain a deeper understanding of the impact of breast cancer and learn about the resources available to support patients, survivors, and their loved ones.

Join the conversation and help spread awareness by sharing this episode and watching the movie with your friends, family, and followers. Together, we can make a difference!

Dear God, I Thank you for covering me and my loved ones this year🙏🏾

This year revealed a lot to me, and gave me a new perspective on the meaning of living life to the fullest! 

I was reminded time and time again, “that what’s for me, is for me”. I had to really lean into that—and lean into it, I did!

From covering carpets, and press junkets, to the relaunch of my podcast, to turning “40”, and everything else in between. 2023 had many ebbs and flows. 

But nothing shook me this year, more than thought that I might have breast cancer. I had been feeling lumps in my breast, so I scheduled an appointment with my doctor, and during the visit, she felt the same thing! She immediately scheduled a mammogram and ultrasound, which was my first🥹 but by God’s Grace, nothing was found in either my mammogram or ultrasound🙏🏾

With all that 2023 brought my way, I’m happy to be walking into the new year, with renewed hope, faith, excitement, intention, and anticipation for what 2024 will bring. 

Thank you, 23! 

I’m ready for more in 2024❤️
